(xvii)  finalize the final report based on consultations with stakeholders and the Asian 
Development Bank (ADB).  

2.  Project financing specialist (international, 10 person-months). The specialist will have 
strong experience in designing and managing renewable energy projects and in designing and 
implementing microfinance in developing countries. The specialist will  

(i)  assess the financial feasibility of the pilot projects, determine an appropriate tariff 
structure, design a cost-effective prepayment system, identify all risks to project 
revenues and costs, and conduct relevant sensitivity analyses;  
(ii)  develop clear mechanisms, strategies, and an overall structure for the financial 
management of projects to promote transparency and long-term sustainability in 
compliance with ADB procedures;  
(iii)  review engineering studies for the pilot projects and provide cost details for all 
project components;  
(iv)  conduct  a  detailed  financial  assessment  of  the  renewable  energy  projects, 
including least-cost financing options;  
(v)  develop an investment plan with the team leader for replicating and scaling up 
renewable energy projects; 
(vi)  develop  links  with  multilateral  financing  institutions  for  establishing  financing 
sources for access to renewable energy; 
(vii)  set up the revolving fund mechanism and develop strategies and structure for its 
management; 
(viii)  conduct a financial assessment of the executing agency that will implement the 
scaling up of renewable energy projects; 
(ix)  help the team leader develop the business models and the knowledge kit; and 
(x)  provide input and assist the team leader in preparing progress and final reports. 

3.  Rural  electrification  engineers  (national, two persons for 16 person-months). The 
engineers  will  have  experience  working  with  governments,  the  private  sector,  and  local 
communities. The position will be based in Manila and require frequent site visits. The engineer 
will  

(i)  support the team leader and project team in (a) arranging travel logistics, (b) 
arranging meetings and workshops, (c) maintaining contacts with stakeholders, 
(d)  obtaining  relevant  country  and  provincial  background  data  for  initial 
assessments, and (e) obtaining follow-up technical data;  
(ii)  support the Department of Energy and the local government in coordinating and 
implementing TA activities;  
(iii)  organize and assist in all required stakeholder consultations;  
(iv)  assist in coordinating communications between the team and the Department of 
Energy;  
(v)  support the team leader in developing and implementing technician training;  
(vi)  supervise civil works and monitor pilot project progress with monthly visits to the 
project sites;  
(vii)  help prepare and implement workshops and dissemination activities;  
(viii)  assist the team leader in developing the business models and the knowledge kit; 
(ix)  provide input and assist the team leader in preparing progress and final reports. 

4.  Procurement specialist (national, 4 person-months). The procurement specialist will 
have experience in procuring microhydro and other renewable energy systems.  The specialist

